        // Smart Value Recapture (SVR) push feeds:
        // SVR is a secondary push channel that runs alongside the primary
        // aggregator and delivers the same price data. The key difference is
        // that SVR-eligible MEV (e.g. oracle-update arbitrage and liquidation
        // value) generated against the consuming protocol is captured by the
        // Chainlink SVR mechanism and shared back with the protocol that
        // reads the feed, rather than being kept entirely by searchers.
        // SVR feeds have slightly higher latency than the primary aggregator
        // (one extra block on the SVR delivery path) and typically run with
        // a marginally wider deviation threshold (e.g. 5 bps where the
        // primary is 2 bps).
        // Reference: https://docs.chain.link/data-feeds/svr-feeds
